news.title: IWG posts revenue of $4.2 billion in 2024
news.para: Its network grew with 899 new centre signings and 624 openings in 2024. Its net financial debt continued to drop and stood at $712 million in 2024 as against $775 million debt it reported in 2023.

news.title: India remains a high-growth real estate market in Asia Pacific region: Report
news.para: According to the Nasdaq-listed real estate consultancy firm, India saw 88 per cent annual rise in investments at USD 3.0 billion. Office assets continued to draw majority of the investments at 47 per cent share, followed by industrial and logistics at 27 per cent share.

news.title: HC summons Bhopal collector in two cases of contempt over RERA
news.para: Both cases pertain to non-compliance of court directives on execution of RRC issued by Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA).

news.title: State government declines formation of metropolitan development body in Kochi
news.para: Replying to a question from TJ Vinod, MLA, LSGD minister MB Rajesh said govt has no plan to form MDA or expand the limit of city corporation.

news.title: Pune civic body launches all-woman team to boost property tax recovery
news.para: On average, PMC collects Rs 2,000 crore as property tax per year. It had set a target of Rs 2,500 crore for the 2024-25 financial year from this levy.

news.title: Housr looks to cross Rs 200 crore revenue in FY26
news.para: Currently operating in five cities, Housr aims to enter Chennai and Mumbai, catering primarily to working professionals.

news.title: Coimbatore to conduct drone-based land survey under DILRMP
news.para: As part of this pilot project, a 10.44 sq. km area will be surveyed using drones, and land records will be updated. Field maps with geo-location points will also be created.

news.title: Ghaziabad: GDA board to take call on developed plots & assimilation of villages
news.para: The meeting, to be chaired by divisional commissioner Hrishikesh Bhaskar Yashod, will take up the proposed assimilation of villages under Hapur Pilakhua and the handover of developed plots to farmers from whom land was acquired for the Madhuban Bapudham housing scheme.

news.title: Kalaburagi district collects Rs 23 crore property tax in FY 2024-25
news.para: The tax demand in gram panchayats, which previously stood at Rs 13 crore, escalated to Rs 36.6 crore, following the initial property survey and valuation exercise.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh government plans two metropolitan regions
news.para: Officials said the urban development and housing department was executing that project that aims to establish the state as a key centre for economic growth.

news.title: SCR plans to transform vacant properties in Hyderabad into commercial hubs
news.para: Railway authorities invited expressions of interest to utilise empty lands at eight prime locations, including Lallaguda, Mettuguda, Arts College, Alwal, and Uppuguda.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad: PCMC's move to add property tax dues on share certificates draws flak
news.para: PCMC officials said they've also written to the District Deputy Registrar of Cooperative Housing Societies of Pune, with the suggestion that those who've not paid their property tax be disallowed from voting in housing society elections.

news.title: Jaipur development body to establish comprehensive data bank of all properties
news.para: The buyers need not apply for the name transfer process as the names of new buyers would be automatically updated in JDA's records, said officials.

news.title: Approval of maps must before building construction: Prayagraj development body
news.para: PDA is holding ‘Manchitra Samadhan Diwas' (Map/Layout Solution Day) every Thursday of the month for building construction in Sangam City.

news.title: Booking for Delhi development body's 828 LIG, EWS flats to start today
news.para: Following the high demand for affordable housing, these flats will be available in addition to the units already part of DDA's ongoing Sabka Ghar Awaas Yojana 2025, stated the authority.

news.title: Lucknow development body to build township in BKT
news.para: The new township is expected to provide housing for at least three lakh people. LDA identified land in 14 villages, including Bhauli, Baurumau, Dhatingra, Goparamau, Lakshmipur and Purwa.

news.title: Existing property owners are also allottees: Gujarat RERA
news.para: The authority ruled in favour of a complainant, ordering a developer to complete the sale deed registration process while recognising the complainant's status as an allottee.

news.title: Civic body can’t cap balcony length citing building bylaws: Karnataka HC
news.para: "The floor area of the balcony shall, however, be taken into consideration while calculating the FAR (floor area ratio), and builders can't claim exemption in respect of this area, as provided under the building bylaws, 2003," Justice NS Sanjay Gowda specified in his order while disposing of a couple of petitions.

news.title: Kolkata: 17-acre plot in New Town worth Rs 800 crore to go for auction
news.para: The plot is in Action Area 1, located between Novotel and the Axis Mall. It is one of the largest parcels that's going for auction in a decade in such a prime area.
